      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DROMORE CASTLE (5) is on debut today and his latest trial was hi most impressive with Noske in the irons. He still looks an immature commodity, though the inside draw suits and he showed good speed in that latest heat. Finds a suitable race on debut and can make an immediate impact. WHITE HOT (8) was good on resumption behind a smart once at Belmont when only 0.3L off the winner. CJP hops on board now and he rates highly on the back of that effort and he's expected to be better again. Can land the knockout blow this time. CAWARRA (7) was sound behind a good winner on resumption and had trialled well coming in. Parnham rides her over WHITE HOT and that's worth noting. The extra journey helps and she can improve. MAURICE'S PRINCESS (6) won her last trial coming into this and looks primed for a bold effort on resumption. UNGOVERNED (4) can feature in the finish with a good draw on resumption.",
